WEBVTT

00:06.574 --> 00:07.675
Frank Wills.

00:07.708 --> 00:08.743
<i>I found a piece of tape</i>

00:08.776 --> 00:10.478
<i>on the parking garage door.</i>

00:10.511 --> 00:11.645
I thought it was a mistake
the first time,

00:11.679 --> 00:13.214
and then it happened again,

00:13.247 --> 00:15.383
<i>and I found another piece
on the sixth floor.</i>

00:15.416 --> 00:18.119
Wow, wow,
you really saved the day here.

00:18.152 --> 00:19.653
Well, I'm just glad
I could represent myself

00:19.687 --> 00:20.721
on behalf of the building.

00:20.755 --> 00:22.156
The president
and the first lady

00:22.189 --> 00:24.458
would like to gift you
a little getaway weekend.

00:24.492 --> 00:26.227
<i>Something to tide you over
until you and the missus</i>

00:26.260 --> 00:28.429
<i>can spring
for the real honeymoon.</i>

00:28.462 --> 00:29.663
And look, it'll be good
to have a little time

00:29.697 --> 00:30.731
away from the city to write

00:30.765 --> 00:32.299
that investigative report,
right?

00:32.333 --> 00:34.368
I could be indicted
for obstruction of justice.

00:34.402 --> 00:36.203
I entrusted the task
of getting me

00:36.237 --> 00:38.172
<i>the written report
to John Dean.</i>

00:39.306 --> 00:40.441
We're gonna have you
tell the truth

00:40.474 --> 00:42.710
in a way
that America likes you.

00:42.743 --> 00:44.545
Convicted
Watergate conspirators

00:44.578 --> 00:47.815
might be first to testify
at the formal hearings.

00:48.048 --> 00:49.316
<i>The ship's going down, John.</i>

00:49.350 --> 00:51.619
It might be best
if I explore other options.

00:51.652 --> 00:54.488
Uh, Mr. Mitchell,
if you ever need anything,

00:54.522 --> 00:55.523
I'm right outside your door.

00:56.791 --> 00:57.758
Oh, here we go.

00:57.792 --> 00:59.093
<i>Should the Nixon administration</i>

00:59.126 --> 01:00.528
be afraid of you,
Mrs. Mitchell?

01:00.561 --> 01:02.096
Well, I think you know
the answer to that.

01:02.630 --> 01:04.765
The committee called.
I'm gonna testify.

01:24.485 --> 01:25.753
Ah, hey, hey, hey.

01:25.786 --> 01:27.788
A-all right, all right,
all right, I'm up.

01:27.822 --> 01:30.157
I'm up, I'm up. Come on.

01:30.191 --> 01:32.159
Come on, Tu--Tuffy, come on.

01:32.193 --> 01:34.495
I got you, okay,
breakfast time.

01:34.528 --> 01:35.763
<i>That was pretty Patti Austin</i>

01:35.796 --> 01:38.165
<i>with a little soul
for your bowl on WOL.</i>

01:38.199 --> 01:40.734
<i>I'll tell it to the hot,
and I'll tell it to the cold.</i>

01:40.768 --> 01:43.804
<i>I'll tell it to the young,
and I'll tell it to the old.</i>

01:43.838 --> 01:45.806
<i>This is Petey Greene's
Washington,</i>

01:45.840 --> 01:48.542
<i>and the whole town's
burnin' a hunk of funk</i>

01:48.576 --> 01:51.479
<i>'cause we got Senate
Watergate hearings this week.</i>

01:51.512 --> 01:53.113
<i>- Ooh, I can't wait to see</i>

01:53.147 --> 01:55.416
<i>which one of these turkeys
is gonna fry.</i>

01:55.449 --> 01:56.650
<i>Speaking of which...</i>

01:56.684 --> 01:57.785
<i>...this next one's going out</i>

01:57.818 --> 02:00.221
<i>to that funky turncoat,
John Dean.</i>

