02:48.736 --> 02:51.238
Tuffy, how do I look?

02:51.272 --> 02:53.674
Like a cat who's gonna be
on the cover of <i>Jet</i> magazine?

02:57.311 --> 02:59.213
Speechless.

02:59.246 --> 03:00.481
<i>So, Mr. Wills,</i>

03:00.514 --> 03:02.283
<i>how's life been for you
since the burglary?</i>

03:02.316 --> 03:03.417
<i>Well, you know how it be.</i>

03:03.450 --> 03:05.819
Sometimes up, sometimes down.

03:08.255 --> 03:09.490
Are you dating anyone?

03:09.523 --> 03:11.458
Married? I don't see a ring.

03:11.959 --> 03:13.761
That depends.

03:13.794 --> 03:15.296
Who you asking for?

03:15.329 --> 03:17.264
Let's just say I have a feeling

03:17.298 --> 03:19.567
our female readers
might be interested.

03:19.600 --> 03:24.271
I was seeing someone
before all this, but, uh,

03:24.305 --> 03:26.240
she broke it off
a couple weeks ago.

03:26.273 --> 03:28.309
Mm, sorry to hear that.

03:28.342 --> 03:29.710
All right, Frank, we're good.

03:29.743 --> 03:31.345
All right.
My man. Thank you, sir.

03:31.378 --> 03:33.314
Yeah, uh, it's copacetic.

03:34.582 --> 03:37.885
Tuffy never really took kind
to her anyway.

03:37.918 --> 03:38.886
Tuffy?

03:38.919 --> 03:40.654
- He's my cat.
- Hmm.

03:40.688 --> 03:42.990
He can always tell when I'm
headed in the wrong direction,

03:43.223 --> 03:45.492
and he has a way
of letting me know it too.

03:45.526 --> 03:46.827
Sounds like a good companion.

03:46.860 --> 03:48.462
Cheap date too.

03:48.495 --> 03:50.364
Tuna's, what,
a quarter these days?

03:52.499 --> 03:53.767
Must be interesting
working in a building

03:53.801 --> 03:56.804
that's become the center
of a national scandal.

03:56.837 --> 03:59.773
Well, actually,
I'm not employed here anymore.

03:59.807 --> 04:01.308
Management let me go
a few weeks ago.

04:01.342 --> 04:04.878
Said I was... becoming
too much of a distraction.

04:06.347 --> 04:09.016
Anyway,
I'm looking for a new gig.

04:09.249 --> 04:11.518
I'm not saying
they shut me out, but...

04:11.552 --> 04:12.920
it's been a lot harder
than I thought it'd be.

04:22.963 --> 04:24.365
What's this?

04:24.398 --> 04:25.799
My number.

04:25.833 --> 04:27.735
Don't get any ideas.

04:27.768 --> 04:29.470
I adjunct over at Howard.

04:29.503 --> 04:32.339
This <i>Jet</i> thing's
just freelance.

04:32.373 --> 04:34.508
I happen to know
that the security department

04:34.541 --> 04:35.743
needs a coordinator.

04:35.776 --> 04:36.877
- Coordinator?
- Mm-hmm.

04:36.910 --> 04:38.612
Oh, shoot,
I can coordinate anything.

04:38.646 --> 04:39.880
See?

04:39.913 --> 04:42.616
Coordinated.

04:42.650 --> 04:43.784
I'll get you an interview.

04:43.817 --> 04:45.519
Mm-hmm. Great.

04:45.552 --> 04:47.721
And, um, after that?

04:47.755 --> 04:49.056
What you mean, "After that?"

04:49.289 --> 04:51.492
I was thinking...

04:51.525 --> 04:53.293
dinner, maybe?

04:53.327 --> 04:55.029
So when I said,
"Don't get any ideas"...

04:55.062 --> 04:56.430
I got 'em anyway.

04:56.463 --> 04:58.799
Ah, okay.

04:58.832 --> 05:00.334
<i>Well, take care, Mr. Wills.</i>

