05:17.351 --> 05:18.719
<i>Man.</i>

05:35.636 --> 05:37.671
Mr. Tuffy,

05:37.705 --> 05:39.106
your lobster has arrived,

05:39.339 --> 05:42.009
courtesy of Howard University.

05:44.712 --> 05:46.413
Hey, you ever met
a Howard girl, Tuffy?

05:47.581 --> 05:49.717
Ooh, this one's nice.

05:49.750 --> 05:51.118
You would've been proud
of me, boy.

05:52.052 --> 05:53.821
Yeah, I made her laugh
and everything, uh,

05:53.854 --> 05:54.922
cracked a few jokes.

05:56.123 --> 05:57.791
But she ain't easy.

05:57.825 --> 05:59.760
She is as smart
as an ankle sprain, boy,

05:59.793 --> 06:00.894
I can tell you that much.

06:05.099 --> 06:07.401
A'ight, boy. Come and get it.

06:09.703 --> 06:11.405
Tuffy?

06:19.413 --> 06:20.447
Tuffy?

06:23.784 --> 06:24.885
Oh, no.

06:24.918 --> 06:26.887
Oh, no, no.

06:26.920 --> 06:28.155
Oh, shit.

06:28.388 --> 06:30.124
No, no, no, no, no.

06:30.157 --> 06:31.125
Tuffy!

06:48.642 --> 06:51.411
Call me once you land
in Little Rock.

06:51.445 --> 06:53.180
Like I said, if you decide

06:53.413 --> 06:55.582
to spend a little longer
down there...

06:55.616 --> 06:57.618
Oh, nice try.
We'll see you on Monday.

07:01.622 --> 07:02.723
Sweetheart.

07:04.658 --> 07:06.593
Well, you look like a lesbian.

07:06.627 --> 07:08.462
Martha.

07:08.495 --> 07:09.963
Well, hi, Lloyd. How are you?

07:09.997 --> 07:11.031
<i>Good. Good.</i>

07:11.064 --> 07:12.766
Glad I caught you
before you left.

07:12.800 --> 07:14.034
Is it true?

07:14.067 --> 07:15.702
You'll be testifying against
the president next week?

07:15.736 --> 07:17.504
Yes, yes, it is true,
but before that,

07:17.538 --> 07:20.107
I am focusing on my
goodwill trip to Pine Bluff.

07:20.140 --> 07:22.442
My daughter and I
are going down there.

07:22.476 --> 07:24.545
We're gonna go to a luncheon
at the historical society.

07:24.578 --> 07:25.979
We'll be the honored guests.

07:26.013 --> 07:27.681
Marty's so excited.

07:27.714 --> 07:28.782
No, I'm not.

07:28.816 --> 07:30.551
She's just being modest.

07:30.584 --> 07:31.652
Get in the car.

07:31.685 --> 07:32.686
Attorney General Mitchell,

07:32.719 --> 07:33.821
how do you feel about your wife

07:33.854 --> 07:35.522
potentially speaking
to the Senate?

07:35.556 --> 07:37.858
Oh, as usual, I support Martha

07:37.891 --> 07:40.027
in whatever she decides to do.

07:40.060 --> 07:42.029
Except there's
no deciding left to do.

07:42.062 --> 07:43.730
I am testifying on Monday.

07:43.764 --> 07:44.865
Right, that's the plan.

07:44.898 --> 07:46.700
Not the plan, the facts.

07:49.970 --> 07:52.072
I really think you should
think about spending

07:52.105 --> 07:53.707
a little more time down there.

07:53.740 --> 07:54.975
Might be very good for you

07:55.008 --> 07:57.811
to get away from all this--
and for Marty too.

07:59.179 --> 08:01.548
Love you. Don't slam the door.

08:04.518 --> 08:06.720
Mr. Mitchell,
do you have any thoughts

08:06.753 --> 08:08.889
on John Dean's
upcoming testimony?

08:08.922 --> 08:11.592
Takes more than a smile
to take on the U.S. government.

08:11.625 --> 08:13.994
Kid's gonna need
a fucking miracle.

08:14.027 --> 08:15.562
<i>Programs regularly scheduled</i>

08:15.596 --> 08:17.798
<i>for this time
will not be seen today</i>

08:17.831 --> 08:18.999
<i>in order
that we might bring you</i>

08:19.032 --> 08:21.501
<i>the following
NBC News Special Report.</i>

08:23.103 --> 08:25.205
Watergate: Senate Hearings.

08:25.239 --> 08:27.741
<i>Mr. Dean,
would you care to describe</i>

08:27.774 --> 08:30.110
<i>what documents have been
made available to you?</i>

08:30.143 --> 08:31.645
As my lawyer
detailed earlier, I--

08:31.678 --> 08:33.146
I don't think you should
say "lawyer."

08:33.180 --> 08:34.581
Just say "my counsel,"

08:34.615 --> 08:37.017
'cause people do not
like lawyers--no offense.

08:37.050 --> 08:38.585
<i>Okay.</i>

08:38.619 --> 08:40.954
As my counsel detailed earlier,

08:40.988 --> 08:43.190
I maintain an extensive log
of clippings

08:43.223 --> 08:46.059
to which I refer
with some regularity.

08:46.093 --> 08:47.594
And how do these clippings

08:47.628 --> 08:48.896
relate to the question,
exactly?

08:48.929 --> 08:50.931
Uh, well, um...

08:50.964 --> 08:54.601
...my meetings with the--
with the president--no?

08:54.635 --> 08:57.671
Uh, I was often dealing

08:57.704 --> 08:59.172
with containment
of press issues--

08:59.206 --> 09:01.642
"Containment"?
I just think that sounds evil.

09:01.675 --> 09:03.677
I mean, what's he working on,
a nuclear reactor?

09:06.580 --> 09:07.881
I agree with that, actually.

09:07.915 --> 09:09.082
- Wh--
- Well, good.

09:09.116 --> 09:10.250
Well, what should
I call it, then?

09:10.284 --> 09:11.785
Don't call it anything.

09:11.818 --> 09:13.587
If a committee member
gives you a question like that,

09:13.620 --> 09:15.022
throw it to me,
and I'll answer it.

09:15.055 --> 09:16.890
No, no.
Won't that make him look weak?

09:21.962 --> 09:26.133
Why don't we take
a little break, okay?

09:26.166 --> 09:28.602
Sounds like the best idea
you've had all day.

09:28.635 --> 09:29.670
Okay.

09:30.637 --> 09:32.105
I think those are the ones.

09:33.607 --> 09:36.043
Baby-baby, I love
how much you're helping,

09:36.076 --> 09:39.246
how much you care, but...

09:39.279 --> 09:42.849
you know, trial prep is what
Shaffer does for a living.

09:42.883 --> 09:45.185
Why don't we let him
take the lead on this?

09:45.218 --> 09:47.754
But this isn't just
some stuffy jury trial, John.

09:47.788 --> 09:50.891
This is a television show
for the American public.

09:50.924 --> 09:51.959
Yeah.

09:54.895 --> 09:57.698
God, I don't know
how you're staying so calm.

09:57.731 --> 09:59.666
Well, 'cause
we're in this together.

10:01.068 --> 10:02.869
Just the two of us
against the world, huh?

10:02.903 --> 10:04.104
Yeah.

10:04.137 --> 10:06.640
Well, three of us now
'cause of the baby.

10:06.673 --> 10:08.075
Hmm?

10:09.242 --> 10:11.178
What--wait, what did you
just say?

10:11.211 --> 10:12.713
- Hmm?
- What? No.

10:12.746 --> 10:14.614
- What'd you just say? That--
- I didn't say anything.

10:14.648 --> 10:16.183
- No. Come on.
- Wait, you said something.

10:16.216 --> 10:17.784
- <i>Are you serious?</i>
- Are you pregnant?

10:17.818 --> 10:19.286
- Wait, really?
- Yup.

10:19.319 --> 10:20.988
Like, seven weeks, really.

10:21.021 --> 10:23.090
Oh, my God.

10:23.123 --> 10:24.324
Oh, jeez,
I don't wanna squash it.

10:24.358 --> 10:27.027
I'm so sorry. I--oh, my God.

10:28.228 --> 10:30.197
Wait, just take these off.
Come here.

10:31.832 --> 10:33.266
Oh, my God.

10:39.206 --> 10:40.207
<i>Whoa! Yay!</i>

10:40.240 --> 10:42.309
<i>- Ha-ha-ha-ha.
- Whoo!</i>

10:42.342 --> 10:44.211
<i>- Oh, yeah!
- Yee-haw!</i>

10:44.244 --> 10:46.113
<i>- Hey!
- Yeah!</i>

10:46.146 --> 10:49.683
<i>♪ Way down in Arkansas ♪</i>

10:49.716 --> 10:51.251
<i>♪ That's where I been
And I'm goin' again ♪</i>

10:51.284 --> 10:53.153
<i>♪ Way down in Arkansas ♪</i>

10:55.989 --> 10:58.091
<i>♪ Whoa, I had a mule
And he weren't no fool</i>

10:58.125 --> 10:59.426
<i>♪ Best mule you ever saw ♪</i>

10:59.659 --> 11:01.261
<i>♪ I heard him say
"I think I'll stay ♪</i>

11:01.294 --> 11:02.929
<i>♪ Down here in Arkansas" ♪</i>

11:02.963 --> 11:04.765
<i>♪ Way down in Arkansas ♪</i>

11:04.798 --> 11:05.832
<i>-♪ Way down in Arkansas... ♪</i>
- Oh, thank you.

11:05.866 --> 11:06.933
You're welcome.

11:08.268 --> 11:10.804
Do you smell that?
Pear trees in bloom.

11:10.837 --> 11:12.706
Smells like death.

11:12.739 --> 11:14.374
We should go later
by Gillan's Market,

11:14.408 --> 11:16.843
get some pears
and some potato salad.

11:16.877 --> 11:18.779
And then we can go
by Sampsons shoe store.

11:18.812 --> 11:21.081
Did I ever tell you
I was briefly a foot model?

11:22.449 --> 11:24.117
Did you come here a lot
when you were a kid?

11:24.151 --> 11:25.285
Oh, no.

11:25.318 --> 11:26.987
The country club
raised the drawbridge on us

11:27.020 --> 11:28.955
the day my daddy skipped town.

11:28.989 --> 11:31.024
My mama tried to charm
and cajole her way back in,

11:31.058 --> 11:32.259
but it was never gonna happen.

11:32.292 --> 11:34.761
These people have
a sixth sense for weakness.

11:34.795 --> 11:37.230
- That sounds scary.
- It is. Keep your guard up.

11:39.199 --> 11:40.901
Oh, my goodness, is that...

11:40.934 --> 11:43.270
Oh, it is. That's Susan Wales
and Henry Daniels.

11:43.303 --> 11:46.273
Hey, whoo, whoo! Henry! Susan!

11:46.306 --> 11:48.809
It's Martha Beall.
Class of '36.

11:49.943 --> 11:52.746
- Get in the car.
- Hey, Henry.

11:53.747 --> 11:55.182
Well, I guess
they didn't recognize me.

12:03.056 --> 12:05.225
Oh, look at the poster.

12:05.258 --> 12:06.493
Wow.

12:09.830 --> 12:10.997
Where are people?

12:11.031 --> 12:12.365
Where <i>are</i> people?

12:13.133 --> 12:16.103
Oh!

12:16.136 --> 12:18.772
I love its gentle warble.

12:18.805 --> 12:20.507
I love its gentle flow.

12:20.740 --> 12:22.509
I love to wind my tongue up.

12:22.742 --> 12:25.078
And I love to let it go!

12:26.847 --> 12:28.148
Oh, my God.

12:28.181 --> 12:29.449
I almost forgot about that.

12:29.483 --> 12:31.184
Oh, I wish I could.

12:32.352 --> 12:34.287
Come here, baby.

12:34.321 --> 12:37.090
This is one of Mama's
oldest friends, Lurleen Landry.

12:37.124 --> 12:38.291
Oh, my goodness.

12:38.325 --> 12:40.427
Oh, looking at you,
it's like--it's like

12:40.460 --> 12:42.329
looking in the past
and seeing an angel.

12:42.362 --> 12:45.832
You are just the perfect
picture of your mother.

12:45.866 --> 12:48.468
I would say attendance
seems a little light.

12:49.870 --> 12:51.505
Yeah, well,
you know, we had some

12:51.538 --> 12:53.273
last-minute cancellations.

12:53.306 --> 12:57.010
It seems your mama is quite the
controversial lady these days.

12:57.043 --> 12:59.446
Mm, I guess I didn't realize
being honest

12:59.479 --> 13:01.248
was so controversial.

13:01.281 --> 13:03.083
Oh, honey, this is Arkansas.

13:03.116 --> 13:05.118
It's too humid for honesty.

13:05.152 --> 13:07.187
You want some lemonade,
sweetheart?

13:07.220 --> 13:08.555
- Can I?
- Of course, darling.

13:08.788 --> 13:10.056
Sure.

13:23.937 --> 13:25.872
<i>And, uh, now, Mr. Magruder,</i>

13:25.906 --> 13:27.307
<i>I'd like
to turn the questions over</i>

13:27.340 --> 13:30.010
