20:12.745 --> 20:14.380
You see where that got her,

20:14.414 --> 20:17.951
lurking around the country club
like some haunted radiator.

20:19.285 --> 20:20.687
I thought you
and Lurleen were friends.

20:20.720 --> 20:22.755
Mm. Are you kidding?

20:22.789 --> 20:24.958
That rich-girl Goody Two-shoes,

20:24.991 --> 20:27.393
ugh, she was
my mama's favorite.

20:27.427 --> 20:29.262
I never heard the end of it.

20:29.295 --> 20:32.832
"Darling, why can't you be
more like Lurleen Landry?

20:32.865 --> 20:36.369
"Lurleen Landry knows
her entire chromatic scale

20:36.402 --> 20:38.271
"and two languages.

20:38.304 --> 20:39.572
Isn't she brilliant?"

20:41.841 --> 20:44.344
But Lord knows
she's had a hard time

20:44.377 --> 20:46.579
with that forehead of hers.

20:46.613 --> 20:49.949
Mom! That is so mean.

20:54.020 --> 20:56.456
We used to have a lot more fun,

20:56.489 --> 20:58.658
before Dad went to work
for Uncle Dick.

21:00.693 --> 21:02.695
Oh, come on, now,
nothing's changed.

21:03.563 --> 21:05.965
What if we stayed
in Pine Bluff a little longer?

21:05.999 --> 21:07.934
You could show me more places
from when you were a kid,

21:07.967 --> 21:10.436
and we could go dress shopping.

21:10.470 --> 21:12.038
I don't know.

21:12.905 --> 21:14.607
You don't have to testify.

21:15.708 --> 21:17.443
You could just tell them
that you changed your mind.

21:17.477 --> 21:19.345
Dad said that
that would be fine.

21:19.379 --> 21:21.981
Uh, well, your daddy
says a lot of things.

21:23.549 --> 21:25.752
Are you guys gonna get
a divorce?

21:25.785 --> 21:27.887
No.

21:27.920 --> 21:30.423
Don't be ridiculous.
We're a family.

21:30.456 --> 21:31.958
Then why are you talking
to the papers all the time,

21:31.991 --> 21:33.726
making Dad into a villain?

21:34.827 --> 21:36.796
Can you--can you just stop?

21:36.829 --> 21:38.965
What would be so bad
about that?

21:38.998 --> 21:40.566
And let Nixon
and the whole lot of them

21:40.600 --> 21:41.834
just get away with it?

21:43.569 --> 21:45.905
Kids at school make fun of me
because of you, Mom.

21:46.739 --> 21:50.009
There's reporters
everywhere I go because of you.

21:51.411 --> 21:53.813
You might think
what you're doing is helping...

21:55.915 --> 21:58.051
...but all I want
is for things to go back

21:58.084 --> 21:59.585
to the way they were.

22:01.721 --> 22:04.357
I just want us
to be normal again.

22:22.341 --> 22:23.476
Mitchell.

22:23.509 --> 22:25.611
<i>Hey, sleepyhead.
Did I wake you?</i>

22:25.645 --> 22:27.380
Oh.

22:27.413 --> 22:30.616
I was wondering
when you'd call.

22:30.650 --> 22:33.352
Sorry,
I was occupied with Marty.

22:33.386 --> 22:35.655
<i>You two having
a hootenanny down there?</i>

22:35.688 --> 22:37.890
No, just a real nice time.

22:40.093 --> 22:43.830
You gonna watch the, uh,
festivities tomorrow?

22:43.863 --> 22:45.765
Probably not.

22:45.798 --> 22:48.401
Although Lurleen Landry
did invite us

22:48.434 --> 22:51.771
over to her house
for a John Dean watch party.

22:51.804 --> 22:53.940
Yeah, well,
maybe you should project it

22:53.973 --> 22:55.441
on her forehead.

22:58.478 --> 23:00.546
She was sweet to me today.

23:00.580 --> 23:02.715
It was actually kind of nice
to see her.

23:02.749 --> 23:05.418
Mm, well, maybe you should go
to her little party.

23:05.451 --> 23:07.920
I mean, the whole country's
gonna be watching.

23:09.489 --> 23:11.991
Listen, I was, um...

23:12.024 --> 23:13.993
I was thinking
maybe you're right.

23:14.026 --> 23:16.696
Maybe we could extend
our stay here a little longer.

23:18.131 --> 23:20.466
Wh-what about your testimony?

23:21.467 --> 23:23.770
Well, maybe it can wait.

23:28.174 --> 23:30.009
I miss you.

23:30.042 --> 23:31.611
I miss you too.

23:32.512 --> 23:34.580
<i>Have fun down there.</i>

23:34.614 --> 23:36.783
- Bye-bye, now.
- <i>Bye-bye.</i>

23:43.956 --> 23:45.491
Everything okay?

23:46.993 --> 23:49.061
Yeah.

23:56.969 --> 24:00.706
Excuse me.

24:00.740 --> 24:02.742
