30:58.057 --> 30:59.525
<i>According to sources familiar</i>

30:59.558 --> 31:01.627
<i>with his opening statement,
the former White House counsel</i>

31:01.860 --> 31:04.563
and admitted coconspirator
intends to level

31:04.597 --> 31:07.199
several criminal claims
against President Nixon,

31:07.233 --> 31:10.336
including obstruction
of justice.

31:10.369 --> 31:11.570
Our coverage of
the Watergate hearings

31:11.604 --> 31:14.473
live from Washington
will continue in a moment.

31:15.641 --> 31:17.309
Oh, I'll get it.

31:19.345 --> 31:21.313
Hey, you fall,
I'm not helping you.

31:22.381 --> 31:24.083
Martha!

31:24.116 --> 31:26.385
Oh, my gosh, I didn't know
if you'd make it.

31:26.418 --> 31:28.187
Come on in!

31:28.220 --> 31:30.556
Look at you
in your precious little dress.

31:30.589 --> 31:32.524
She picked it out.

31:32.558 --> 31:34.026
Ma'am.

31:34.059 --> 31:35.294
Hello. Uh, here.

31:35.327 --> 31:36.962
You wanna put that down
over here?

31:36.996 --> 31:38.197
Thank you.

31:38.230 --> 31:40.366
Oh, look at that.

31:40.399 --> 31:41.567
<i>Isn't that darling?</i>

31:41.600 --> 31:43.902
<i>You and your sweet mama.</i>

31:43.936 --> 31:45.170
I wanted you to see that

31:45.204 --> 31:47.606
before I gave it
to the historical society.

31:47.640 --> 31:49.141
You know how she always
wanted to be a part of things.

31:49.174 --> 31:51.910
- Oh, yeah.
- Now she really can be.

31:51.944 --> 31:55.080
Oh, Lurleen, I just, um...

31:55.114 --> 31:57.650
I just wanted to say
thank you for having me here.

31:57.683 --> 32:00.419
It's been real nice
to be back home.

32:00.452 --> 32:02.421
Oh, Martha Beall,

32:02.454 --> 32:05.391
you always have a home
in Pine Bluff.

32:05.424 --> 32:08.260
Come on, you want a drink?
God knows you need a drink.

32:20.406 --> 32:22.074
They're ready for you,
Mr. Dean.

32:27.246 --> 32:28.247
<i>All right.</i>

32:31.016 --> 32:33.352
Time to knock them dead
in there, champ.

32:43.362 --> 32:44.463
Let's go.

32:49.335 --> 32:50.369
I can't.

32:51.403 --> 32:52.638
What's that?

32:52.671 --> 32:55.040
C--I can't.
We-we have to call it off.

32:56.575 --> 32:58.110
<i>We can't call it off.</i>

32:58.143 --> 33:00.112
<i>Y-you're up in five minutes.
Stop fucking around.</i>

33:00.145 --> 33:02.047
I'm not joking. I can't do it!

33:02.081 --> 33:03.382
I can't go up there.

33:07.619 --> 33:09.655
That is perfect.

33:09.688 --> 33:11.390
Two of you wanted to do this
without a lawyer,

33:11.423 --> 33:13.325
and, what,
now you're chickening out?

33:13.359 --> 33:16.328
They will see right through me.

33:16.362 --> 33:19.398
I'm a fraud. Don't you get it?
No one will believe me.

33:19.431 --> 33:21.300
<i>I mean, this is just too--
this is too much.</i>

33:21.333 --> 33:23.035
Hey, this is not
about you anymore.

33:23.068 --> 33:24.636
This is about everything
that we have worked towards,

33:24.670 --> 33:27.306
and you're not going
to fuck this up now, okay?

33:29.141 --> 33:30.542
Here's what we're gonna do.

33:30.576 --> 33:33.011
You're gonna stop whatever
this is, this blubbering,

33:33.045 --> 33:34.079
pull yourself together.

33:34.113 --> 33:35.414
We'll walk
into that room together,

33:35.447 --> 33:37.416
and you'll give your testimony
just like we practiced.

33:37.449 --> 33:38.751
Remember the three things?

33:38.784 --> 33:42.321
No slumping, no fumbling
your words, no excuses.

33:44.490 --> 33:46.291
Do you think this is hard?

33:47.559 --> 33:49.395
Because this is not hard.

34:00.706 --> 34:02.574
Put on your coat, and let's go.

34:40.112 --> 34:43.148
Mr. Dean,
would you raise your hand?

34:43.182 --> 34:45.217
<i>Do you swear to tell
the truth, the whole truth,</i>

34:45.250 --> 34:47.486
<i>nothing but the truth,
so help you God?</i>

34:47.519 --> 34:49.221
I do.

34:49.254 --> 34:51.557
<i>You may be seated.</i>

34:51.590 --> 34:53.625
<i>All right, good morning,
ladies and gentlemen.</i>

34:53.659 --> 34:56.628
Welcome to the 12th day
of public testimony

34:56.662 --> 34:59.131
for the Watergate subcommittee.

34:59.164 --> 35:02.401
I can't help but notice
that our featured speaker here,

35:02.434 --> 35:06.505
Mr. John Dean, is seated
without counsel present.

35:06.538 --> 35:08.140
Is that a mistake, Sir?

35:08.173 --> 35:10.108
Uh, no, sir, it is not.

35:10.142 --> 35:11.743
My counsel is present
in the room,

35:11.777 --> 35:14.580
but I intend to testify alone.

35:16.548 --> 35:18.183
Son, excuse me for asking,

35:18.217 --> 35:21.286
but why in the hell
would you do that?

35:24.723 --> 35:28.160
Because I intend to tell
the truth, Mr. Chairman.

35:28.193 --> 35:30.329
I do not need a lawyer
to help me with that.

35:32.331 --> 35:36.468
Well, gee, aren't you a keeper
of the gosh-durn flame?

35:38.270 --> 35:39.605
All right,
would you care to read

35:39.638 --> 35:41.707
your prepared statement, son?

35:41.740 --> 35:43.275
Yes, sir. Thank you.

35:44.743 --> 35:48.280
Chairman Ervin,
members of the committee,

35:48.313 --> 35:49.681
I would like to commence

35:49.715 --> 35:51.517
with a general description
of the atmosphere

35:51.550 --> 35:55.387
that existed in the White House
prior to June 1972.

35:55.420 --> 35:57.155
To one who was
in the White House

35:57.189 --> 36:00.225
and became somewhat familiar
with its inner workings,

36:00.259 --> 36:02.528
the Watergate matter
was an inevitable outgrowth

36:02.561 --> 36:04.363
of a climate
of excessive concern

36:04.396 --> 36:05.831
over the political impact

36:05.864 --> 36:09.568
of demonstrators,
excessive concern over leaks,

36:09.601 --> 36:12.404
coupled with a do-it-yourself
White House staff

36:12.437 --> 36:15.240
<i>with no regard for the law.</i>

36:15.274 --> 36:17.643
<i>It was not until I joined
the White House staff</i>

36:17.676 --> 36:19.378
<i>in July of 1970</i>

36:19.411 --> 36:22.180
<i>that I had fully realized
the strong feelings</i>

36:22.214 --> 36:23.715
<i>that the president
and his staff...</i>

36:35.360 --> 36:36.562
I think he's doing great,
don't you?

36:36.595 --> 36:37.529
Yeah.

36:37.563 --> 36:38.664
<i>However, the fact
that many of these elements</i>

36:38.697 --> 36:39.965
<i>culminated with the creation</i>

36:40.198 --> 36:42.334
<i>of a covert
intelligence operation</i>

36:42.367 --> 36:45.537
<i>was not by conscious design--
rather an accident of fate.</i>

36:47.439 --> 36:49.641
Now Mr. Dean, did it worry you

36:49.675 --> 36:52.277
that this Liddy fellow
came up with schemes

36:52.311 --> 36:55.847
involving kidnapping,
prostitution, mugging,

36:55.881 --> 36:57.683
and all the rest of it?

36:57.716 --> 36:59.518
Yes, sir, it did,
and for the record,

36:59.551 --> 37:02.854
I recall Liddy saying that
the girls would be high-class

37:02.888 --> 37:04.456
and the best in the business.

37:07.526 --> 37:09.261
He's so dreamy.

37:09.294 --> 37:11.296
I smoked a cigarette
with him once.

37:11.330 --> 37:13.398
Do kids in D.C. smoke?

37:13.432 --> 37:14.666
If they want to.

37:14.700 --> 37:16.001
<i>Were you surprised
when you heard</i>

37:16.234 --> 37:18.503
<i>about the break-in
on June 17th?</i>

37:18.537 --> 37:20.939
I was more appalled
than surprised.

37:22.407 --> 37:23.909
He's lying.

37:23.942 --> 37:25.844
Seems like he's
telling the truth.

37:25.877 --> 37:27.012
How do you know, Harold?

37:27.245 --> 37:28.580
You've never been to D.C.

37:28.614 --> 37:31.383
I've been to Harrisburg once.

37:31.416 --> 37:32.985
It's all smoke and mirrors,
you see.

37:33.018 --> 37:34.486
Now, Dean, he's a climber.

37:34.519 --> 37:36.655
He's not the best I've
ever seen--that'd be Lyndon--

37:36.688 --> 37:38.790
but he's not the worst either.

37:38.824 --> 37:40.659
You know how D.C. lawyers are.

37:40.692 --> 37:43.295
The only difference
between them and gigolos is,

37:43.328 --> 37:45.797
a gigolo only screws
one person at a time.

37:45.831 --> 37:48.634
Well, you should know.
You're married to one.

37:51.470 --> 37:54.473
Jesus Christ, would you two
quiet down already?

37:56.842 --> 37:58.844
You're just like him.

37:58.877 --> 38:01.880
<i>Get on TV every day
like a fool.</i>

38:03.348 --> 38:04.950
You're bringing down
our president.

38:07.352 --> 38:08.754
Wow, golly,

38:08.787 --> 38:11.623
didn't realize
I was so powerful.

38:11.657 --> 38:14.860
Golly.
You're a Southern girl, huh?

38:14.893 --> 38:17.362
In the South,
we believe in America.

38:17.396 --> 38:20.966
<i>We don't need no cheap
road act coming here</i>

38:20.999 --> 38:25.003
and holding court like
you're some kinda damn queen.

38:25.871 --> 38:27.906
Loudmouth fucking cunt.

38:27.939 --> 38:29.074
Clarence!

38:30.809 --> 38:32.778
Think you've had enough.

38:32.811 --> 38:34.446
It's all right. It's all right.

38:34.479 --> 38:36.815
It's probably best that
Clarence doesn't remember this

38:36.848 --> 38:38.483
in the morning.
Sit down, sit down.

38:38.517 --> 38:41.586
I'm gonna get myself a drink.
I'll get you a fresh one too.

39:03.508 --> 39:04.976
If you were to die,

39:05.010 --> 39:07.345
how would you want it
to happen?

39:07.379 --> 39:09.514
Um, drowning, maybe?

39:11.550 --> 39:13.518
Marty, come here, honey.

39:16.488 --> 39:17.923
We need to get going.

39:17.956 --> 39:19.691
What? But we just got here.

39:19.725 --> 39:21.426
I know, but we're gonna
get an early flight tomorrow,

39:21.460 --> 39:22.794
so I want us to go now.

39:22.828 --> 39:24.896
You-you're still testifying?

39:24.930 --> 39:25.897
Mm-hmm.

39:25.931 --> 39:27.733
Everything all right?

39:27.766 --> 39:28.934
Let's be on our way.

39:28.967 --> 39:30.736
So you made me come down here,

39:30.769 --> 39:32.738
and then once I actually
start to have fun

39:32.771 --> 39:34.372
and have friends for once,
you wanna leave?

39:34.406 --> 39:35.674
Excuse me, Marty,
would you consider

39:35.707 --> 39:36.942
keeping your voice down?

39:36.975 --> 39:38.443
Excuse me, Lurleen.

39:38.477 --> 39:40.045
Do you know
what you should consider?

39:40.078 --> 39:41.379
Bangs.

39:42.380 --> 39:45.150
Why-why can't you just listen
to Dad and let it go?

39:45.383 --> 39:47.819
Why do you have to make
our lives miserable?

39:47.853 --> 39:49.554
You do not know
what you're talking about.

39:49.588 --> 39:52.124
Now, get in the car right now,
without another word.

40:04.402 --> 40:06.772
Uh, all right,
calm down, Marty.

40:06.805 --> 40:09.508
Are you sure
that's what Mommy said?

40:09.541 --> 40:11.443
She's coming home to testify?

40:11.476 --> 40:13.445
<i>I don't wanna go home.
I don't want her to testify.</i>

40:13.478 --> 40:16.148
Okay, well, I'll be here
when you get back tomorrow

40:16.181 --> 40:19.417
and we-we'll talk
about it then, okay?

40:19.451 --> 40:21.119
- <i>Okay, bye.</i>
- Okay, darling.

40:29.995 --> 40:33.832
Diana, get me Senator Gurney.

40:36.501 --> 40:38.503
Thank you
for your testimony, Mr. Dean.

40:38.537 --> 40:41.473
I'm sure we all
appreciate your candor.

40:41.506 --> 40:44.843
<i>All right, the committees
will stand in recess</i>

40:44.876 --> 40:48.747
at the close of business
tomorrow instead of Friday,

40:48.780 --> 40:52.217
until we reconvene again
on Tuesday, July tenth.

40:54.486 --> 40:56.822
Mr. Dean, Mr. Dean.
How do you feel?

40:56.855 --> 40:58.523
Everyone seems to
think you did pretty darn good.

40:59.558 --> 41:00.659
John.

41:00.692 --> 41:03.128
Thank you very much.
Thanks. All right.

41:03.161 --> 41:04.162
Thank you very much. Thank you.

41:07.065 --> 41:08.099
John.

41:10.168 --> 41:11.636
Please.

41:13.171 --> 41:14.139
Thank you.

41:14.172 --> 41:16.007
<i>And so the
committee finishes its work,</i>

41:16.041 --> 41:17.542
<i>and the public
and the Senate committee</i>

41:17.576 --> 41:19.477
<i>will have to judge
between Mr. Dean</i>

41:19.511 --> 41:22.581
<i>and those who contradict him,
the conflicting parties.</i>

41:22.614 --> 41:24.216
For George Herman
and Daniel shore,

41:24.249 --> 41:27.619
this is Nelson Benton,
CBS News, Washington.

41:29.788 --> 41:31.556
And I was so nervous beforehand.

41:31.590 --> 41:33.892
I'm so sorry I freaked out,
you know, but once I--

41:33.925 --> 41:35.794
<i>once I locked in,
man, when I locked in,</i>

41:35.827 --> 41:37.596
<i>I was in the flow.</i>

41:37.629 --> 41:38.930
<i>You see Gurney's face when I--</i>

41:38.964 --> 41:40.565
<i>when I threw
that question back at him?</i>

41:40.599 --> 41:43.001
<i>Oh, my God. It was priceless.</i>

41:43.835 --> 41:47.939
I am gonna fix myself a G&T.

41:49.908 --> 41:51.543
You want one?

41:51.576 --> 41:53.612
Oh, wait, that's right.
I'm sorry.

41:53.645 --> 41:54.779
<i>We should go
to that restaurant</i>

41:54.813 --> 41:55.780
<i>with the singing waiters.</i>

41:55.814 --> 41:56.915
<i>What's it called? Luciano's?</i>

41:56.948 --> 41:58.016
<i>I love that place.</i>

41:59.618 --> 42:00.919
<i>Oh, God, that's good.</i>

42:02.254 --> 42:03.688
Are you sad you can't have
a G&T?

42:03.722 --> 42:06.992
You want me just to fix you
the T or a tea?

42:07.025 --> 42:08.260
I can--I can put the kettle on.

42:08.293 --> 42:10.528
You want it?

42:10.562 --> 42:12.697
It's over. You did it.

42:12.731 --> 42:14.766
Mo.

42:14.799 --> 42:16.167
Moser, what's--

42:18.103 --> 42:20.305
What's going on, hmm?

42:20.538 --> 42:24.009
I'm sorry, the reporters
were mobbing me.

42:24.042 --> 42:25.977
It's not the reporters.

42:26.011 --> 42:27.078
Um...

42:31.016 --> 42:32.317
Okay.

42:34.219 --> 42:36.588
Well, I was sitting there
behind you,

42:36.621 --> 42:39.758
and I just started thinking,

42:39.791 --> 42:42.027
"Oh, gosh,
once Watergate is over

42:42.060 --> 42:45.764
"and your image is salvaged,

42:45.797 --> 42:48.900
where does that leave, um, me?"

42:50.635 --> 42:53.939
Baby, look, if I can
stay out of jail, we can--

42:53.972 --> 42:55.073
we can move past this.

42:55.106 --> 42:56.741
We can get past anything.

42:57.809 --> 42:59.811
Into your future. Yes.

42:59.844 --> 43:01.112
<i>No, come on.</i>

43:03.682 --> 43:06.718
I think I'm just realizing
I can't

43:06.751 --> 43:11.323
just play the dutiful wife
in your story, okay?

43:11.356 --> 43:14.059
Just picking out your clothes
and smiling for the cameras.

43:15.260 --> 43:16.695
I thought I could, but I can't.

43:16.728 --> 43:19.965
I think I'll, um, lose myself.

43:26.705 --> 43:28.273
I just don't--

43:28.306 --> 43:30.942
Um, I lost the...

43:30.976 --> 43:32.344
baby.

43:34.980 --> 43:36.381
What?

43:38.083 --> 43:39.217
When?

43:39.250 --> 43:41.252
Last night and this morning.

43:41.286 --> 43:43.154
- <i>Oh, my God.</i>
- And it's a long process,

43:43.188 --> 43:45.090
<i>- apparently.</i>
- Oh, my God.

43:45.123 --> 43:46.324
I'd like to be alone.

43:58.737 --> 44:00.105
<i>Frank, are you there?</i>

44:02.707 --> 44:04.175
<i>It's Janelle.</i>

44:04.209 --> 44:06.678
Coming, coming.

44:22.160 --> 44:23.895
I've been calling you all day.

44:25.830 --> 44:26.998
Mind if I come in?

44:27.032 --> 44:28.366
Yeah, come on in.

44:30.035 --> 44:33.338
Ooh, it's, uh, chilly in here.

44:33.371 --> 44:36.241
Yeah, I been leaving
the window open for Tuffy.

44:37.075 --> 44:38.743
What happened to you
last night?

44:38.777 --> 44:40.145
You left, didn't say goodbye.

44:40.178 --> 44:42.414
Yeah, sorry,
I forgot to tell you.

44:47.452 --> 44:49.454
I heard about the Howard job.

44:51.256 --> 44:53.224
What happened?

44:53.258 --> 44:55.427
The man on the phone says

44:55.460 --> 44:59.197
I'm a-a controversial
political figure.

45:00.298 --> 45:01.966
He says I got notoriety.

45:02.901 --> 45:04.302
Ain't that a trip?

45:04.335 --> 45:07.772
I ain't even got no car,
but yet I got notoriety.

45:07.806 --> 45:09.841
It's that damn
university president.

45:09.874 --> 45:12.077
He is a secret Nixon freak.

45:12.110 --> 45:13.711
Janelle, come--

45:13.745 --> 45:16.014
<i>And listen,
I promise we will fight this.</i>

45:16.047 --> 45:17.348
- Stop.
- <i>Okay?</i>

45:17.382 --> 45:18.850
<i>There's plenty
of political groups on campus,</i>

45:18.883 --> 45:20.785
and they will gladly
nail his ass to the ground.

45:20.819 --> 45:22.420
J-Janelle, stop. Please.

45:24.923 --> 45:26.324
I don't wanna fight anymore.

45:29.160 --> 45:31.329
I'm going back to Georgia.

45:31.362 --> 45:32.497
What?

45:32.730 --> 45:33.932
Yeah,
rent's a lot cheaper there,

45:33.965 --> 45:35.166
and my mama's
getting pretty old.

45:35.200 --> 45:37.802
No. No.

45:37.836 --> 45:41.206
Look, listen, I know
it is tough right now,

45:41.239 --> 45:44.075
but you can't just give up.

45:44.109 --> 45:46.077
Give up? Give up on what?

45:46.111 --> 45:47.479
On your friends
looking at me like--

45:47.512 --> 45:49.481
like I'm some kinda dummy?

45:49.514 --> 45:51.850
You're real smart,
you know that?

45:53.118 --> 45:55.086
And smart people like you
got this way of--

45:55.120 --> 45:57.055
of-of-of turning things over
